							</a>
						</div> <!-- .comment-meta -->

					</div>
		
					<div class="comment-content">
						<p>@Vetri The function expression, var myName = function () {console.log (“Rich”);}, is not actually hoisted. Instead, if you initialize it after the var myName = &#8220;Rich&#8221; initialization, the myName variable is assigned a new value, which is the function.</p>
<p>It looks like this when the code is executed:<br />
var myName;<br />
myName = &#8220;Rich&#8221;;</p>
<p>// Then it is assigned a new value, the function<br />
myName = function () {console.log (&#8220;Rich&#8221;);}</p>
						
											</div>

