					<div class="comment-content">
						<p>Hi Richard,</p>
<p>thank you for the article, I wasn&#8217;t aware of the scope for &#8216;this&#8217; inside timeouts and intervals.<br />
I just wanted to point out a small problem in one of the examples, the variable names in the following example, should be surrounded by double quotes, as now they&#8217;re checked as properties inside window:</p>
<p>console.log(myName in window);<br />
console.log(firstName in window);</p>
<p>Should be:</p>
<p>console.log(&#8220;myName&#8221; in window); // true<br />
console.log(&#8220;firstName&#8221; in window); // true</p>
						
