						<img alt='' src='http://1.gravatar.com/avatar/74e4ea3fd64e56918e056b399d5f84d8?s=40&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g' srcset='http://1.gravatar.com/avatar/74e4ea3fd64e56918e056b399d5f84d8?s=80&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-40 photo' height='40' width='40' />						</div>

						<div class="comment-meta flexbox-item">					
							<a href="http://javascriptissexy.com/javascript-variable-scope-and-hoisting-explained/#comment-165856" class="comment-author titleFont">
								Shaikhul															</a>
							<a href="http://javascriptissexy.com/javascript-variable-scope-and-hoisting-explained/#comment-165856" class="comment-time metaText" title="November 29, 2013 at 7:28 am">
								<time pubdate datetime="2013-11-29T07:28:41+00:00">6 years ago</time>
							</a>
						</div> <!-- .comment-meta -->

					</div>
		
					<div class="comment-content">
						<p>Function Declaration Overrides Variable Declaration When Hoisted &#8211; OK</p>
<p>But variable assignment overrides the function declaration &#8211; not OK.</p>
<p>ex.<br />
var hoistMe = &#8216;hoistme';<br />
function hoistMe () {};<br />
typeof hoistMe; // &#8220;function&#8221;</p>
						
											</div>

					<div class="comment-actions">
