								sankar															</a>
							<a href="http://javascriptissexy.com/javascript-variable-scope-and-hoisting-explained/#comment-309270" class="comment-time metaText" title="September 3, 2018 at 8:34 am">
								<time pubdate datetime="2018-09-03T08:34:30+00:00">10 months ago</time>
							</a>
						</div> <!-- .comment-meta -->

					</div>
		
					<div class="comment-content">
						<p>var myName = &#8220;Richard&#8221;; // This is the variable assignment (initialization) that overrides the function declaration.</p>
<p>function myName () {<br />
console.log (&#8220;Rich&#8221;);<br />
}</p>
<p>console.log(typeof myName); // string</p>
<p>Though variable assignment is done it is not overriding the function declaration.<br />
console.log(typeof myName);  is giving function as output in chrome.</p>
						
											</div>

